      "content": "Don't be too quick to dismiss your symptoms, though. Ice and immobilization can be helpful, but if you're still experiencing pain and swelling after 48 hours, that's a good indication to get it checked out. And trust me, you don't want to ignore the possibility of a stress fracture - it's better to catch it early and prevent further damage. Ibuprofen can mask the pain, but it's not a substitute for a proper diagnosis.",
